The paper presents deterministic algorithms for the maximum matching problem in dynamic graphs, which involves data structures and algorithms for maintaining and updating a matching in a graph as edges are added or removed. This falls under the category of dynamic algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which are commonly studied in the subfield of approximation algorithms (cs.AL). Additionally, the paper presents results for bipartite graphs, which are often studied in the subfield of combinatorics and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper presents polylogarithmic update time algorithms, which are commonly studied in the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC).
